1
00:00:07,951 --> 00:00:10,062
Ooh, smell that air!

2
00:00:11,057 --> 00:00:12,510
Grass and lemonade,

3
00:00:12,915 --> 00:00:16,480
and a little bit of mint,
a hint of mint, must be the 1920s.

4
00:00:17,034 --> 00:00:19,983
You can tell what year
it is just by smelling?

5
00:00:20,165 --> 00:00:21,067
0h, yeah!

6
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:25,000
Or maybe that big vintage car
coming up the drive gave it away.

7
00:00:32,260 --> 00:00:34,877
<i>The professor's luggage,
Richard, step lively.</i>

8
00:00:37,005 --> 00:00:38,685
Good afternoon, Professor Peach.

9
00:00:38,785 --> 00:00:40,164
Hello, Greeves old man.

10
00:00:40,997 --> 00:00:42,122
Ah... Reverend!

11
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:44,663
Professor Peach! Beautiful day.

12
00:00:44,763 --> 00:00:46,821
Lord's in his heaven,
all's right with the world.

13
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:48,324
Reverend Golightly.

14
00:00:48,605 --> 00:00:52,204
Lady Eddison requests that you make
yourselves comfortable in your rooms.

15
00:00:52,304 --> 00:00:55,351
Cocktails will be served on the lawn
from half past four.

16
00:00:55,451 --> 00:00:59,094
You go on up. I need to check
something in the library. Alone.

17
00:00:59,194 --> 00:01:02,937
It's supposed to be a party. All
this work, it'll be the death of you!

18
00:01:03,442 --> 00:01:05,252
Never mind Planet Zog.

19
00:01:05,352 --> 00:01:08,562
A party in the 1920s,
that's more like it!

20
00:01:08,662 --> 00:01:11,292
Trouble is, we haven't been invited.

21
00:01:11,392 --> 00:01:13,626
0h, I forgot, yes, we have!

22
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:17,382
I was right.

23
00:01:17,894 --> 00:01:21,695
Kept secret all these years...
It's unbelievable!

24
00:01:22,293 --> 00:01:24,680
But why didn't they ask...?
Heavens!

25
00:01:25,195 --> 00:01:26,378
Oh, it's you.

26
00:01:26,681 --> 00:01:28,823
I was just doing a little research...

27
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:32,543
I say, what are you doing
with that lead piping?

28
00:01:34,014 --> 00:01:36,800
But that's impossible...
No! No-!

